-- China National Cotton Exchange to Tighten Price Controls, Cut Volatility
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-04T08:46:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/china-national-cotton-exchange-to-tighten-price-controls-cut-volatility.html
China National Cotton Exchange said
it will take measures to stabilize cotton prices and reduce
volatility, the exchange said in a statement on its website
today.  The exchange will curb cotton price manipulations and
tighten risk controls, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
